# Header checks
#
# This are regular expression filters
#
# It's a good practice to put a # and a Reason after the action, in
# that way you will be able to identify which rule baned a mail to
# analyze it 

# Expression				        Action  No  Reason
/^Subject:\s.* [Pp]uta .*/		REJECT (#1) No se permiten Mala palabras

# Ban sender/return forgery
/^((Envelope\-)?From|Return\-Path):\s*[^<]*<[^@]+@[^@>]+>[^<]*<[^@]+@[^@>]+>/     REJECT No double address in the From or Return-path header allowed

# Ban subject less emails
/^Subject:\s*$/		REJECT No se permiten mensajes sin asunto / No subject-less email please
